headlines.description: — The 76ers needed a lift from a big man out of Kansas each time the undermanned Suns made a run at the lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid, Kelly Oubre Jr. lead 76ers past Phoenix 112-100 for fourth straight win

headlines.description: — Mark Williams scored 27 points, Gordon Hayward had 23 and the Charlotte Hornets snapped a three-game losing streak with a 125-124 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mark Williams scores 27 as Hornets rally to edge Pacers 125-124

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 26 points, Paolo Banchero added 25 points, 10 assists and seven rebounds and the Orlando Magic blasted the Los Angeles Lakers 120-101 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner scores 26, leads Magic over Lakers 120-101

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Once Trae Young and the surging Atlanta Hawks found their offensive rhythm in the second half, there seemed little Zion Williamson, Brandon Ingram or the rest of the New Orleans Pelicans could do to keep up.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 22 points, 12 assists lead the Hawks past the Pelicans 123-105

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 32 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead the Boston Celtics to a 124-112 win over the Brooklyn Nets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics outlast Nets 124-114 behind Tatum and Holiday's double-doubles

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 12 of his 26 points in the fourth quarter to lead the Houston Rockets to a 107-89 win over the Sacramento Kings on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks has big fourth quarter, scores 26 to lead Rockets over Kings 107-89

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored 15 of his season-high 25 points in a dominant third-quarter stretch, and the Minnesota Timberwolves pulled away to beat the Utah Jazz 123-95 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns takes over in 3rd quarter as Timberwolves beat Jazz 123-95

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 28 points, 16 rebounds and nine assists, Michael Porter Jr. scored a season-best 27 and the Denver Nuggets overcame the loss of point guard Jamal Murray to beat the Chicago Bulls 123-101 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic just shy of triple-double, Porter scores 27 to lead Nuggets over Bulls 123-101
